{"word":"ἀρχικός","slug":"ἀρχικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρχικός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀρχή'><el>ἀρχή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for rule, royal</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>fit for rule, skilled in government</i> or <i>command</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>having command of</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}